datasets.name: ee59747e
queryLines:
-- ============================================================================
-- Pipeline Update Lifecycle Summary
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- This query processes raw event logs to extract pipeline update state,
-- compute lifecycle duration, and determine the final status of each update.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Step 1: Extract and normalize relevant fields from the raw event log
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
WITH curated_event_log AS (
    SELECT
        origin.pipeline_id AS pipeline_id,
        origin.pipeline_name AS pipeline_name,
        origin.update_id AS pipeline_update_id,
        id,
        timestamp,
        level,
        event_type,
        details
    FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs
),

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Step 2: Parse `update_progress` events to extract state field
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
parsed_update_progress AS (
    SELECT
        *,
        FROM_JSON(details, 'struct<update_progress: struct<state: string>>') AS upd
    FROM curated_event_log
    WHERE event_type = 'update_progress'
),

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Step 3: Identify the last known state for each update_id
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
last_status_per_update AS (
    SELECT
        pipeline_id,
        pipeline_update_id,
        pipeline_name,
        upd.update_progress.state AS last_update_state,
        timestamp,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY pipeline_update_id
            ORDER BY timestamp DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM parsed_update_progress
    QUALIFY rn = 1
),

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Step 4: Compute start and end timestamps and total duration
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
update_durations AS (
    SELECT
        pipeline_id,
        pipeline_name,
        pipeline_update_id,

        -- Capture the start of the update
        MIN(CASE WHEN event_type = 'create_update' THEN timestamp END) AS start_time,

        -- Capture the end of the update based on terminal states
        MAX(CASE
            WHEN event_type = 'update_progress'
             AND FROM_JSON(details, 'struct<update_progress: struct<state: string>>').update_progress.state IN ('COMPLETED', 'FAILED', 'CANCELLED')
            THEN timestamp
        END) AS end_time,

        -- Calculate duration in seconds
        TIMESTAMPDIFF(
            SECOND,
            MIN(CASE WHEN event_type = 'create_update' THEN timestamp END),
            MAX(CASE
                WHEN event_type = 'update_progress'
                 AND FROM_JSON(details, 'struct<update_progress: struct<state: string>>').update_progress.state IN ('COMPLETED', 'FAILED', 'CANCELLED')
                THEN timestamp
            END)
        ) AS duration_seconds

    FROM curated_event_log
    WHERE event_type IN ('create_update', 'update_progress')
      AND pipeline_update_id IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY pipeline_id, pipeline_name, pipeline_update_id
    HAVING start_time IS NOT NULL AND end_time IS NOT NULL
)

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Step 5: Join final status and duration metrics, filter to latest state
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SELECT
    s.pipeline_id,
    s.pipeline_name,
    s.pipeline_update_id,
    d.start_time,
    d.end_time,
    d.duration_seconds,
    s.last_update_state AS pipeline_update_status
FROM last_status_per_update s
JOIN update_durations d
  ON s.pipeline_id = d.pipeline_id
 AND s.pipeline_update_id = d.pipeline_update_id
ORDER BY d.end_time DESC;

datasets.name: 9f3b86f2
queryLines:
-- ============================================================================
-- Step 1: Identify the latest update_id per pipeline from event_log_raw
-- ============================================================================
WITH latest_update AS (
  SELECT 
    origin.pipeline_id,
    origin.update_id AS latest_update_id
  FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs AS origin
  WHERE origin.event_type = 'create_update'
  ORDER BY timestamp DESC 
  -- LIMIT 1 -- remove if you want to get all of the update_ids
),

-- ============================================================================
-- Step 2: Parse the planning_information JSON into a structured format
-- ============================================================================
parsed_planning AS (
  SELECT
    origin.pipeline_name,
    origin.pipeline_id,
    origin.flow_name,
    lu.latest_update_id,
    from_json(
      details:planning_information,
      'struct<
        technique_information: array<struct<
          maintenance_type: string,
          is_chosen: boolean,
          is_applicable: boolean,
          cost: double,
          incrementalization_issues: array<struct<
            issue_type: string,
            prevent_incrementalization: boolean,
            operator_name: string,
            plan_not_incrementalizable_sub_type: string,
            expression_name: string,
            plan_not_deterministic_sub_type: string
          >>
        >>
      >'
    ) AS parsed
  FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs AS origin
  JOIN latest_update lu 
    ON origin.update_id = lu.latest_update_id
  WHERE details:planning_information IS NOT NULL
),

-- ============================================================================
-- Step 3: Extract the chosen technique from the array 'technique_information'
-- ============================================================================
chosen_technique AS (
  SELECT
    pipeline_name,
    pipeline_id,
    flow_name,
    latest_update_id,
    FILTER(parsed.technique_information, t -> t.is_chosen = true)[0] AS chosen_technique,
    parsed.technique_information AS planning_information
  FROM parsed_planning
)

-- ============================================================================
-- Final Step: Select and display the results
-- ============================================================================
SELECT
  pipeline_name,
  pipeline_id,
  flow_name,
  latest_update_id,
  chosen_technique.maintenance_type,
  chosen_technique,
  planning_information
FROM chosen_technique
ORDER BY latest_update_id DESC;

datasets.name: 0cfc2c44
queryLines:
WITH first_pipeline_id AS (
  SELECT first(origin['pipeline_id'], TRUE) AS id
  FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs
)

SELECT
  sku_name,
  billing_origin_product,
  usage_date,
  collect_set(identity_metadata.run_as) AS users,
  SUM(usage_quantity) AS `DBUs`
FROM
  system.billing.usage
WHERE
  usage_metadata.dlt_pipeline_id = (SELECT id FROM first_pipeline_id)
GROUP BY
  sku_name,
  billing_origin_product,
  usage_date;

datasets.name: 9ab40944
queryLines:
-- ============================================================================
-- Flow Metrics and Duration Calculation
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- This query extracts flow progress events, computes start/end times and final
-- statuses, aggregates metrics, and calculates duration as (end - start) in seconds.
-- ============================================================================

WITH flow_progress_raw AS (
  SELECT 
    origin.pipeline_name         AS pipeline_name,
    origin.pipeline_id           AS pipeline_id,
    origin.flow_name             AS table_name,
    origin.update_id             AS update_id,
    timestamp,
    details:flow_progress.status AS status,

    -- Extract numeric metrics from the flow progress details
    TRY_CAST(details:flow_progress.metrics.num_output_rows AS BIGINT)      AS num_output_rows,
    TRY_CAST(details:flow_progress.metrics.num_upserted_rows AS BIGINT)    AS num_upserted_rows,
    TRY_CAST(details:flow_progress.metrics.num_deleted_rows AS BIGINT)     AS num_deleted_rows,
    TRY_CAST(details:flow_progress.data_quality.dropped_records AS BIGINT) AS num_expectation_dropped_rows,

    -- Extract JSON array of data quality expectations
    FROM_JSON(
      details:flow_progress.data_quality.expectations,
      SCHEMA_OF_JSON("[{'name':'str', 'dataset':'str', 'passed_records':42, 'failed_records':42}]")
    ) AS expectations_array

  FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs
  WHERE event_type = 'flow_progress'
    AND origin.flow_name IS NOT NULL
    AND origin.flow_name != 'pipelines.flowTimeMetrics.missingFlowName'
),

aggregated_flows AS (
  SELECT
    pipeline_name,
    pipeline_id,
    update_id,
    table_name,

    -- Earliest start time for relevant statuses
    MIN(CASE WHEN status IN ('STARTING', 'RUNNING', 'COMPLETED') THEN timestamp END) AS start_timestamp,

    -- Latest end time for relevant statuses
    MAX(CASE WHEN status IN ('STARTING', 'RUNNING', 'COMPLETED') THEN timestamp END) AS end_timestamp,

    -- Most recent terminal status per flow
    MAX_BY(status, timestamp) FILTER (
      WHERE status IN ('COMPLETED', 'FAILED', 'CANCELLED', 'EXCLUDED', 'SKIPPED', 'STOPPED', 'IDLE')
    ) AS final_status,

    -- Aggregate numeric metrics
    SUM(COALESCE(num_output_rows, 0))              AS total_output_records,
    SUM(COALESCE(num_upserted_rows, 0))            AS total_upserted_records,
    SUM(COALESCE(num_deleted_rows, 0))             AS total_deleted_records,
    MAX(COALESCE(num_expectation_dropped_rows, 0)) AS total_expectation_dropped_records,

    -- Consolidate expectations arrays
    MAX(expectations_array)                        AS total_expectations

  FROM flow_progress_raw
  GROUP BY pipeline_name, pipeline_id, update_id, table_name
)

SELECT 
  af.pipeline_name,
  af.pipeline_id,
  af.update_id,
  af.table_name,
  af.start_timestamp,
  af.end_timestamp,
  af.final_status,

  -- Calculate duration in seconds, rounded to nearest integer
  CASE 
    WHEN af.start_timestamp IS NOT NULL AND af.end_timestamp IS NOT NULL THEN
      ROUND(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MILLISECOND, af.start_timestamp, af.end_timestamp) / 1000)
    ELSE NULL
  END AS duration_seconds,

  af.total_output_records,
  af.total_upserted_records,
  af.total_deleted_records,
  af.total_expectation_dropped_records,
  af.total_expectations

FROM aggregated_flows af

-- Optional: filter to latest update only
WHERE af.update_id = (
  SELECT update_id
  FROM aggregated_flows
  ORDER BY end_timestamp DESC
  LIMIT 1
)

ORDER BY af.end_timestamp DESC, af.pipeline_name, af.pipeline_id, af.update_id, af.table_name;

datasets.name: 8378c4ab
queryLines:
with latest_update as (
  SELECT origin.update_id as id
    FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs 
    WHERE event_type = 'create_update' 
    ORDER BY timestamp DESC 
    limit 1 -- remove if you want all of the update_ids
)
SELECT
  details:flow_definition.output_dataset as flow_name,
  details:flow_definition.input_datasets as input_flow_names,
  details:flow_definition.flow_type as flow_type, 
  details:flow_definition.schema, -- the schema of the flow 
  details:flow_definition -- overall flow_definition object
FROM main__build.dbdemos_pipeline_bike.pipeline_bike_event_logs inner join latest_update on origin.update_id = latest_update.id
WHERE details:flow_definition IS NOT NULL 
ORDER BY timestamp
LIMIT 10;
